						               													<description>55 playing cards of irregular four-sided shape, and each card can have 0, 1, 2, 3 or 4 different colour segments, plus a letter of the alphabet. &amp;#10;All games proposed use the same 6 simple matching rules to decide which moves are legal or not.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can play with them all traditional card games, but the rulebook offers also 11 new and very different games to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) Pentago (for 2-4 players)&amp;#10;By matching your cards by colour with that on the table, you must play all your cards or block your opponents from playing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2) Polygo Word (for 2-6 players)&amp;#10;The object is to score as many points as possible by forming a single dictionary word of 2 or more letters, using always at least 1 letter from a previous word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3) Polygo Challenge 2001&amp;#10;A solo game, where you must build a 7x7 block of cards, each matching by colour segment with at least another near card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4) Astack (for 2-4 players)&amp;#10;Stacking cards you must play all your cards first, or force your opponent to pick more cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5) Solo 1&amp;#10;A solitaire game: object is to transfer all cards from the deck to three colums, and then to a final play pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;6) Solo 2&amp;#10;Beat your own score by drawing cards and playing them on the table only if you can find at least one match with the previously placed cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;7) Polywords (for 2-5 players)&amp;#10;By placing cards in a crossword style you must form any to or more letter dictionary words.&amp;#10;  &amp;#10;8) 5-Up (for 2-6 players)&amp;#10;A Pentago variant, where cards must by played inside a block a 5x5 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;9) Polygo Whist (for 2-8 players)&amp;#10;Win most Tricks and score as high as possible by playing every hand the highest ranking Trump or the highest leading Suit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;10) Polygo Rummy (for 2-6 players)&amp;#10;Be the first to meld all your cards of the same Suit with at least one segment of the same colour.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;11) Polygo Shape Puzzles (for 1-8 players)&amp;#10;Try to beat your score or of your opponents by placing cards to form one of five possible shapes with matching cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
